text: Jamaal Anthony Hansen, known professionally as INFJ Kenzo, is an American rapper, record producer, entrepreneur, and founder of the Irvine, California- based conglomerate talent and entertainment agency OTAON Media. He serves as the artistic director of OTAON Media. Born in Santa Monica, California, and raised in the Kansas City metropolitan area and Iowa, INFJ Kenzo began his musical career in the early 2020s. He co-founded the record label OTAON Entertainment in 2020 and released his debut studio album, The Wage of Better Angels: A Treatise to the Truth, in 2022. == References == Category:American rappers
